{{Infobox language | name = Czech Sign Language | states = [[Czech Republic]] | region = Eastern Europe | speakers = 12,000 |date=2011 census | ref = e18 |speakers2=10,000 (2014)<ref name=e18/> | familycolor = Sign | fam1 = [[French Sign Language family|French Sign]] | fam2 = [[Austro-Hungarian Sign Language|Austro-Hungarian Sign]] | iso3 = cse |glotto=czec1253 |glottorefname=Czech Sign Language }}
'''Czech Sign Language''' is the [[sign language]] of the [[deaf]] community in the [[Czech Republic]]. It presumably emerged around the time of the first deaf school in [[Bohemia]] (1786). It belongs to the French sign-language family and is partially intelligible with [[French sign language]].<ref>http://www.ethnologue.com/language/cse</ref> Despite the similarity of oral Czech and Slovak, it is not particularly close to [[Slovak Sign Language]].
