{{Use New Zealand English|date=August 2013}}
A '''district plan''' is a statutory planning document of [[Territorial authorities of New Zealand|New Zealand's territorial authorities]].

Mainly covering [[land use]]/[[zoning]] questions, they have been required since the advent of the [[Resource Management Act 1991]].<ref>{{cite book |chapter=A Guide to Using the District Plan |chapter-url= http://www.aucklandcity.govt.nz/council/documents/districtplannorthshore/text/section1-guide-to-using-district-plan.pdf |chapter-format=PDF |title=Auckland Council District Plan Operative North Shore Section 2002}}</ref> They are updated periodically, though major revisions and plan changes are usually not produced very often, partly due to the large-scale legal battles that often follow proposed changes.

