'''Suctorial''' pertains to the [[adaptation]] for sucking or suction,<ref>Dictionary.com, "suctorial," in Dictionary.com Unabridged (v 1.1). Published by Random House, Inc. http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/suctorial. Accessed: February 09, 2009</ref> as possessed by marine [[parasite]]s such as the [[Cookiecutter shark]],<ref name=floridamus>{{cite web|url=http://www.flmnh.ufl.edu/fish/Gallery/descript/Megamouth/megamouth.htm|title=Megamouth Shark- Parasites|last=Carol Martins & Craig Knickle|publisher=Florida Museum of Natural History|accessdate=2009-02-09}}</ref> specifically in a specialised lip organ enabling attachment to the host.
Suctorial organs of a different form are possessed by the [[Solifugae]] [[arachnid]]s, enabling the climbing of smooth, vertical surfaces.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Cushinga, P.E. |author2=Jack O. Brookharta |author3=Hans-Joachim Kleebeb |author4=Gary Zitob |author5=Peter Payne|year=2005|title=The suctorial organ of the Solifugae|journal=Arthropod Structure & Development|publisher=ScienceDirect|volume=34|issue=4|pages=397–406|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science?_ob=ArticleURL&_udi=B6W66-4HD8BCN-2&_user=10&_rdoc=1&_fmt=&_orig=search&_sort=d&view=c&_acct=C000050221&_version=1&_urlVersion=0&_userid=10&md5=b721cc2f3e55efdd6899dac5e3ef2817|accessdate=2009-02-09|doi=10.1016/j.asd.2005.02.002|first1=P}}</ref>
Another variation on the suctorial organ can be found as part of the [[Tongue|glossa]] [[proboscis]] of [[Masarinae]] (pollen wasps), enabling nectar feeding from the deep and narrow corolla of flowers.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Krenn, H.W. |author2=Volker Mauss |author3=John Plant|year=2002|title=Evolution of the suctorial proboscis in pollen wasps|journal=Arthropod Structure & Development |publisher=ScienceDirect|volume=31|issue=2|pages=103–120|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science?_ob=ArticleURL&_udi=B6W66-4777803-3&_user=10&_rdoc=1&_fmt=&_orig=search&_sort=d&view=c&_acct=C000050221&_version=1&_urlVersion=0&_userid=10&md5=9c6252acd772cdabce3e18f78130846a|doi=10.1016/S1467-8039(02)00025-7|first1=H |pmid=18088974}}</ref>
